  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper version: 0.1.0b13\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nVyper ignores scientific notation in decimal literals, e.g.,\r\n```\r\n@public\r\ndef foo() -> decimal:\r\n    return 2e-8\r\n```\r\nand instead just returns the part before the `e` (in this case 2).\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nI don't think scientific notation is necessary for decimals, so probably just disallow this.",
